# Purpose

Social Groups define how individual relationships develop into larger social structures.

In Paradiso:

> Characters do not only have relationships with individuals.

They also exist within communities.

A group may influence:

- What information spreads.
- Who is trusted.
- Who is isolated.
- How conflicts develop.
- How decisions are made.

---

# GROUP-001 Group Definition

A Social Group is:

> A collection of characters connected by repeated interaction, shared goals, or mutual trust.

Groups are emergent.

AI must not randomly assign permanent groups.

